        "parts": [
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "117 - "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "وَقَالَ أَبُو جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ: «إِنَّ رَسُولَ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "آلِهِ كَانَ يُكْثِرُ اَلسِّوَاكَ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "لَيْسَ بِوَاجِبٍ فَلاَ يَضُرُّكَ تَرْكُهُ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " فِي"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:12:10",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/12/117",
      "text": [
        " فَرْطِ اَلْأَيَّامِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.117 - Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) said:\n\"Indeed, the Messenger of Allah (sw) frequently used siwak (tooth cleaning), but it is not obligatory, so it will not harm you if you leave it for a few days”."
        ]
      }
    },
